[SN]TITLE[SN]
Guinea Pig Club memorial 'a fitting tribute' to airmen

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
A memorial to airmen who suffered disfiguring war injuries is a fitting tribute, a 93-year-old veteran who helped raise the funds for it said.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
2 November 2016 Last updated at 21:00 GMT
Dr Sandy Saunders, who was badly burned in a crash in 1945, is a member of the Guinea Pig Club, so called because its members underwent pioneering surgery by war-time doctors.
A statue in the men's honour was unveiled earlier by The Duke of Edinburgh, Prince Philip.
